nz\n  |isbn=3-7637-5871-2}}\n* {{cite book\n  |last=Spielberger\n  |first=Walter\n  |title=Von der Zugmachine zum Leopard 2 \u2014 Geschichte der Wehrtechnik bei Krauss-Maffei\n  |publisher=Bernard & Graefe Verlag\n  |year=1980\n  |language=German\n  |location=M\u00fcnchen\n  |isbn=3-7637-5203-X}}\n* {{cite book\n  |last=Westermeyer\n  |first=Paul W.\n  |url=http://www.usmc.mil/news/publications/Documents/U.S.%20Marines%20in%20Battle%20Al-Khafji%20%20PCN%20106000400_1.pdf\n  |format=PDF\n  |title=U.S. Marines in Battle: Al-Khafji, 28 January \u2013 1 February 1991\n  |publisher=History Division, U.S. Marine Corps\n  |location=Washington D.C., United States of America}}\n* {{cite book\n  |last=Zaloga\n  |first=Steven J.\n  |title=Modern Soviet Armor: Combat Vehicles of the USSR and Warsaw Pact Today\n  |publisher=Prentice Hall\n  |year=1979\n  |location=Edinburgh, United Kingdom\n  |isbn=0-13-597856-4\n  |url-access=registration\n  |url=https://archive.org/details/modernsovietarmo00zalo\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  |last=Zaloga\n  |first=Steven J.\n  |title=The M47 and M48 Patton Tanks\n  |publisher=Osprey\n  |year=1999\n  |location=Oxford, United Kingdom\n  |isbn=1-85532-825-9}}\n* {{cite book\n  |last=Zaloga\n  |first=Steven J.\n  |title=T-54 and T-55 Main Battle Tanks 1944\u20132004\n  |publisher=Osprey\n  |year=2004\n  |location=Oxford, United Kingdom\n  |isbn=1-84176-792-1}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons|AMX-30}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081118200202/http://maquetland.com/v2/index.php?page=vision&id=159&type=photos MAQUETLAND AMX-30 Page]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20121006012709/http://www.armyrecognition.com/forum/viewtopic.php?p=7129#7129#7129 GIAT's Overview Manual for the AMX-30 \u2013 English Version]\n\n{{featured article}}\n{{French Army Vehicle}}\n{{ColdWarFrenchAFVs}}\n{{ModernFrenchAFVs}}\n{{Cold War tanks|style=wide}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Amx-30}}\n[[Category:Main battle tanks of France]]\n[[Category:Main battle tanks of the Cold 