{"title_page": "Canoeing at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's C-1 500 metres", "text_new": "{{CanoeingAt1988SummerOlympics}}\nThe '''men's C-1 500 metres''' event was an open-style, individual [[canoe]]ing event conducted as part of the [[Canoeing at the 1988 Summer Olympics]] program.\n\n==Medallists==\n{| class=wikitable\n|align=center bgcolor=gold| [[Image:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px|Gold]] '''Gold'''\n|align=center bgcolor=silver| [[Image:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px|Silver]] '''Silver'''\n|align=center bgcolor=cc9966| [[Image:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px|Bronze]] '''Bronze'''\n|-\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Olaf Heukrodt]]|GDR|1988 Summer}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Micha\u0142 \u015aliwi\u0144ski]]|URS|1988 Summer}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Martin Marinov]]|BUL|1988 Summer}}\n|}\n\n==Results==\n\n===Heats===\n18 competitors were entered, but three withdrew prior to the heats. Held on September 26, the top three finishers in each heat moved on to the semifinals with the others were relegated to the repechages. Heat 2 was scheduled, but not held with all three competitors advancing to the semifinals due to an insufficient number of entrants.\n\n{| style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n|colspan=4 align=left|'''Heat 1'''\n|-\n|width=30|1.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Micha\u0142 \u015aliwi\u0144ski]]|URS|1988 Summer}} ||width=80| 1:51.90 || '''QS'''\n|-\n|2.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Martin Marinov]]|BUL|1988 Summer}} || 1:52.74 || '''QS'''\n|-\n|3.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Olaf Heukrodt]]|GDR|1988 Summer}} || 1:53.73 || '''QS'''\n|-\n|4.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Petr Proch\u00e1zka]]|TCH|1988 Summer}} || 1:58.09 || QR\n|-\n|5.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Jan Pinczura]]|POL|1988 Summer}} || 2:00.20 || QR\n|-\n|6.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Jang Yeong-Cheol]]|KOR|1988 Summer}} || 2:13.21 || QR\n|-\n|colspan=4 align=left|'''Heat 2'''\n|-\n| -||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Narcisco Su\u00e1rez]]|ESP|1988 Summer}} || - || '''QS'''\n|-\n| -||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Larry Cain]]|CAN|1988 Summer}} || - || '''QS'''\n|-\n| -||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[James Terrell (canoer)|James Terrell]]|USA|1988 Summer}} || - || '''QS'''\n|-\n|colspan=4 align=left|'''Heat 3'''\n|-\n|1.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Attila Szab\u00f3 (Hungarian canoer)|Attila Szab\u00f3]]|HUN|1988 Summer}} || 1:54.83 || '''QS'''\n|-\n|2.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Aurel Macarencu]]|ROU|1988 Summer}} || 1:54.95 || '''QS'''\n|-\n|3.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Eric Jamieson]]|GBR|1988 Summer}} || 1:55.66 || '''QS'''\n|-\n|4.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Ivan \u0160abjan]]|YUG|1988 Summer}} || 2:00.55 || QR\n|-\n|5.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Timo Gr\u00f6nlund]]|FIN|1988 Summer}} || 2:01.60 || QR\n|-\n|6.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Yasunobu Kanada]]|JPN|1988 Summer}} || 2:10.20 || QR\n|}\n\n===Repechages===\nTwo repechages were held on September 26 with the top three finishers in each repechage advancing to the semifinals. The second repechage was scheduled, but not held with both competitors advancing to the semifinals.\n\n{| style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n|colspan=4 align=left|'''Repechage 1'''\n|-\n|width-30|1.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Petr Proch\u00e1zka]]|TCH|1988 Summer}} ||width=80| 2:00.64 || '''QS'''\n|-\n|2.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Timo Gr\u00f6nlund]]|FIN|1988 Summer}} || 2:01.48 || '''QS'''\n|-\n|3.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Jang Yeong-Cheol]]|KOR|1988 Summer}} || 2:05.85 || '''QS'''\n|-\n|4.||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Yasunobu Kanada]]|JPN|1988 Summer}} || 2:06.31 ||\n|-\n|colspan=4 align=left|'''Repechage 2'''\n|-\n| -||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Ivan \u0160abjan]]|YUG|1988 Summer}} ||width=80| - || '''QS'''\n|-\n| -||align=left|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Jan Pinczura]]|POL|1988 Summer}} || - || '''QS'''\n|}\n\n===Semifinals===\nThree semifinals were held on September 28 with the top three finishers of each semifinal advancing to the final.\n\n{| style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n|colspan=4 al