        = <!--<ref> </re> -->\n| area_note               =\n| area_water_percent      =\n| area_rank               =\n| area_blank1_title       =\n| area_blank2_title       =\n<!-- square kilometers -->\n| area_total_km2          = \n| area_land_km2           =\n| area_water_km2          =\n| area_urban_km2          =\n| area_rural_km2          =\n| area_metro_km2          =\n| area_blank1_km2         =\n| area_blank2_km2         =\n<!-- hectares -->\n| area_total_ha           = \n| area_land_ha            =\n| area_water_ha           =\n| area_urban_ha           =\n| area_rural_ha           =\n| area_metro_ha           =\n| area_blank1_ha          =\n| area_blank2_ha          =\n<!-- dunams used in Middle East articles only -->\n| dunam_link              = <!-- which dunam to link -->\n| area_total_dunam        = \n| area_land_dunam         =\n| area_water_dunam        =\n| area_urban_dunam        =\n| area_rural_dunam        =\n| area_metro_dunam        =\n| area_blank1_dunam       =\n| area_blank2_dunam       =\n| length_km               =\n| width_km                =\n| dimensions_footnotes    =\n| elevation_footnotes     =\n| elevation_m             =\n| population_footnotes    =<ref name=dampop/>\n| population_total        = 47,339\n| population_as_of        = 2004\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      =\n| population_note         =\n| timezone1               =\n| utc_offset1             =\n| timezone1_DST           =\n| utc_offset1_DST         =\n| postal_code_type        =\n| postal_code             =\n| area_code_type          =\n| area_code               =\n| iso_code                =\n| website                 = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n'''Barzeh''' ({{lang-ar|\u0628\u0631\u0632\u0629}}, also transliterated  '''Berz\u00e9''') is a [[Municipalities of Damascus|municipality]] and a neighborhood to the north of [[Damascus]], Syria.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2012/07/18/us-syria-crisis-damascus-idUSBRE86H0BI20120718|title=Battles break out near Syrian presidential palace|author=Khaled Yacoub Oweis|date=18 July 2012|accessdate= 19 July 2012|work=[[Reuters]]}}</ref> According to the [[Central Bureau of Statistics (Syria)|Syria Central Bureau of Statistics]], Barzeh had a population of 47,339 in the 2004 census.<ref name=dampop>[http://www.cbssyr.org/new%20web%20site/General_census/census_2004/NH/TAB01-1-2004.htm Damascus city population]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe municipality has been [[Cities and towns during the Syrian civil war#Barzeh|active]] in the [[Syrian civil war]]. The [[Sunni]] Barzeh neighborhood is largely pro-opposition. However, the neighboring [[Alawite]] \"slum\" Esh al-Warwar is largely pro-government.<ref name=\"conciliatory\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-25781412|title=In Syria, few conciliatory signs as peace talks loom\n|author=Lina Sinjab|date=18 January 2014|accessdate= 9 July 2016|work=[[BBC]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/features/2011/10/20111011154631737692.html|title=Assad's Alawites: An Entrenched Community |author=Nir Rosen|date=12 October 2011|accessdate= 9 July 2016|work=[[Al-Jazeera]]}}</ref> The Barzeh area has been under truce between the rebels and government since 2014.<ref name=\"conciliatory\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/02/26/syria-local-ceasefires_n_4856336.html|title=Syrian Government Sees An End Game, Block By Block|author=Joshua Hersh|date=26 February 2014|accessdate= 9 July 2016|work=[[Huffington Post]]}}</ref> On 1 April 2015, the rebels ([[Jaish al-Islam]] and the [[Free Syrian Army]]'s First Brigade) launched a military campaign to expel the [[Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant|Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]] from the Barzeh and [[Qaboun]] neighborhoods,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://now.mmedia.me/lb/en/NewsReports/565135-isis-encroaches-on-east-damascus|title=ISIS encroaches on east Damascus |author=|date=17 April 2015|accessdate=29 August 2016|work=NOW}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.zamanalwsl.net/news/9717.html|title=Damascus: Islam Army attacks ISIS bases in Qaboun, Barzeh neighborhoods|author=|date=17 April 2015|accessdate=29 August 2016|work=Zaman al-Wasl}}</ref> which ended in success three days later.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://aranews.net/2015/04/syrian-rebels-defeat-isis-in-damascus/|title=Syrian rebels defeat ISIS in Damascus|author=|date=20 April 2015|accessdate=29 August 2016|work=Ara News}}</ref> On 8 February 2016, an IS car bomb targeting a government officer's club killed eight people in Masakin Barzeh.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/10/world/middleeast/isis-syria-car-bomb.html?_r=0|title=ISIS, in a First, Says It Was Behind Attack in Syrian Capital|author=Anne Barnard|date=9 February 2015|accessdate=29 August 2016|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref>\nOn 29 May 2017 the Syrian government regained control of the entire district.<ref>{{cite news|title=Evacuation of rebels from Damascus district complete, city governor says|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-barzeh-idUSKBN18P1L4|accessdate=29 May 2017|work=Reuters|date=29 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Neighborhoods==\n*Al-Abbas (pop. 23,112)\n*Barza al-Balad (pop. 31,634)\n*Ish al-Warwar (pop. 20,458)\n*Al-Manara (pop. 10,199)\n*Masakin Barzeh (pop. 15,705)\n*An-Nuzha (pop. 6,488)\n\n==Education==\nThe [[Higher Institute for Applied Sciences and Technology]] has its main campus in the Hameesh area<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.facebook.com/hiast.edu.sy/ |title=HIAST |date= |work=Facebook |publisher= |accessdate=18 April 2018}}</ref> of Barzeh.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Damascus}}\n\n\n[[Category:Neighborhoods of Damascus]]\n\n\n{{DamascusSY-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlem